{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01KBeRhAy2U83mcEuKvHrPHh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Session 11 complete. Added `ricochet_ray` strategy in `agent/active_operators.py` that solves e5790162.\n\n**Pattern:** A single shooter cell on a grid edge fires a ray that ricochets 90° at each isolated marker cell. Each marker color has a learned turn direction (cw/ccw), inferred from the example pairs.\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Detects shooter as the unique non-bg color whose count *increases* in output\n- Initial ray direction is perpendicular to the edge the shooter sits on\n- For each pair, brute-forces over (initial_direction × cw/ccw per marker color) to find a consistent turn-mapping; aggregates constraints across pairs\n- Trail painting stops at the grid edge\n- **Placed before `_try_recolor_sequential`** because that strategy was matching the background-to-shooter recoloring as a single connected component and producing identity-like garbage; ricochet_ray's strict isolation requirements make it safe to try first\n\n**Result:** 24/40 → 25/40 (60.0% → 62.5%), +1 rule learned (`rule_032`). `run_task.py` regression still CORRECT."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":373,"cache_read_input_tokens":162234,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":373},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2cacda48-5f60-4a2f-a847-59e549259f88","uuid":"2a77ac64-89c4-471a-bbf0-106ce851e279"}
